data.title: The Gaslight Anthem signs with Crush Music
data.meta_description: The Gaslight Anthem signs with Crush Music for management
data.text:
New York-based inspo-pop with a side of rock, R&B and disco collective Sammy Rae & The Friends are releasing their debut album âSomething For Everybodyâ this fall.

The genre-blending band are known for their memorable and inclusive live performances and are slated for an extensive North American tour starting September.

Artist manager Jake Kinney has launched Nashville-based management company Pioneer Artists.

The company's first signee is American country singer Conner Smith, who will be co-managed by Chris Kappy of Make Wake Artists.

32 new (or extended) tours in the Tour Directory, including Fred again.., SEVENTEEN, Tinashe, The KID LAROI, Morrissey & more

Sentric Music & Cooking Vinyl Publishing announced an administration agreement and formed a creative joint venture.

To co-publishing JV will cover new signings, creative projects, funding, sync & more.
